The paper discusses security vulnerabilities and countermeasures in the healthcare environment related to the adoption of mobile technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper focuses on the security and compliance challenges of introducing mobile devices in healthcare. The paper also discusses software engineering practices and countermeasures, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the regulatory compliance aspect, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
